Join experts in the building and maintenance of sustainable road networks across east, central and South Africa at Argus Africa Roads 2018 on 6-8 March in Tanzania. The event offers you a chance to build long term relationships with the most influential decision-makers across Kenya, Tanzania, Uganda, Malawi, Zambia, Namibia, Mozambique and more. You can also meet with global and regional road construction groups, road authorities, contractors, financiers, asphalt, bitumen, aggregates producers, traders and innovative service providers. Confirmed attendees include senior executives from Ministry of Works, Transport and Communication, Tanzania,Kenya National Highways Authority,ANE National Roads Administration, Mozambique, Road Development Agency, Zambia,Roads Authority Namibia,African Ports and Corridor Holdings (APCH), DSM Corridor Group (DCG), African Infrastructure Investment Managers, Kenya Roads Board, LAPSSET Corridor,Bechtel,Namibia Roads Contractor Company (RCC),Kenya Investment Authority, Shell,Jey Oil Africa,JFM Construction, Barloworld South Africa, IMCD South Africa,DuPont,Sasol,Maurerand more! This is the only roads maintenance and construction conference in Africa to address upcoming and ongoing projects, bitumen and asphalt technologies and innovations and much more. Register now for your chance to identify new opportunities in the road construction business. The event will also offer a high level showcase of the projects, innovations, materials and technologies to ensure investment in a safe and sustainable road and highways network for Africa. For more information contact bitumen@argusmedia.com or call +44 (0) 20 7780 4341 Please visit the website for further information: http://www.argusmedia.com/events/argus-events/europe/argus-africa-roads/home/?utm_source=Partner&utm_medium=listing&utm_campaign=Lon-Conf-AAR18-cr Logistical Information:
